text:
Hi, what does this mean?
I cant find any documentation about this.

There's an option for logo modules to have fallback text for the company name. I think this is saying that you are missing the use_account_default parameter so that it will default to the settings the user has already configured in the account.

You'd need to inspect the code in the logo module, except it looks like it's in the HubSpot folder which wouldn't be editable unless you clone it down to a child theme.

Are you working with a child theme of a HubSpot theme and customizing the header? If so, you'd need to also clone the logo module to the child to fix the warning. It's just a warning though, so it will still work the way it's coded.

thank you for your response, I am actually just trying to learn more about dnd. I am pointing to the default HubSpot logo module and wanted to keep it that way, but I'll look into the developer info to find out more.
You're welcome, happy to help if you run into other questions
